Gauteng youngster Jeffrey Kruger clinched this year’s Lotus Challenge championship in the last of the season’s 18 races, to take the category title for the second year in a row. We asked him some questions. Q: What is your everyday occupation? A: I work at the BMW plant in Rosslyn, designing low cost intelligent automation systems. Q: What do you consider your biggest motorsport achievement thus far? A: Winning the European Golf Cup championship in 2015 and the 2018 Falken Polo Cup title here at home. Q: What are your racing plans for next year? A: I will contest the...